title: A Popular History of Ireland: from the Earliest Period to the Emancipation of the Catholics, Book 07
creator: Thomas D'Arcy McGee
description: LibriVox recording of A Popular History of Ireland: from the Earliest Period to the Emancipation of the Catholics, Book 07, by Thomas D'Arcy McGee. Read by Sibella.] Thomas D’Arcy McGee was an Irish refugee and a father of the Canadian confederation. His work on Irish history is comprehensive, encompassing twelve books; Book 7 subtitled “Unionized Crowns of England and Ireland”, addresses the Tudor period, particularly the actions of Woolsey and Henry VIII, before the Reformation, in 1541. (Summary by Sibella Denton) For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B audiobook of Complete Series
